The paper deals with face deidentification, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and privacy and security (cs.CR). The use of generative neural networks (GNNs) is a key aspect of the proposed approach, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves the evaluation of the proposed method using automated recognition tools and human annotators, which could be considered as a multimedia-related task (cs.MM).
